Agent:

  * Add RPC authentication.
  * Add maximum aging to LRU cache.
    * Reap all aged out entries when cache nears fill (pop/push to check).
  * Add SetConfig/GetConfig and all other methods to Notch device API.
  * Session dashboard. Session info should also be available via an RPC.
  * Counters and counter data export for monitoring.

Client:

  * Request timeouts.
  * Record RPC latencies.
  * Gather other RPC statistics.
  * Use RPC statistics to influence load balancer, strategies such as:
    * Inverse RTT
    * Error Averse

Tools:

  Bundle these with the agent/client distribution, in examples/.

  * Mr. CLI - A multi-router command-line interface.
